---
title: Irish Sirloin Steak in a Red Wine Jus with charred broccoli and hazelnut crumb
description: A jus is a name for a gravy made with meat juices—and in this case red wine. It's a sauce that makes an excellent pairing for richer meats such as the sirloin steak in this dish.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/HF_Y23_R13_W15_IE_IESB14717-2_Main__10high-39042f27.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.ie/recipecards/card/beef-sirloin-in-a-red-wine-jus-64073977df6297bb5beef0ec-2bc50954.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.ie/recipes/irish-sirloin-steak-in-a-red-wine-jus-64073977df6297bb5beef0ec
